The paper deals with the problem of pattern matching in a weighted sequence, which is a type of uncertain data. This problem is a central problem in computer science and is related to data structures and algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves probability theory and information theory, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper presents an efficient algorithm for constructing an index and computing the weighted prefix table and all covers of a weighted sequence, which are related to computational complexity and combinatorics, respectively. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
